n class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hni1665702758666.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hni1665702758666.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hni1665702758666.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hni1665702758666\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"hni1665702758666__uxmlreader_444880\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">UXMLREADER is an internal Uniface component that enables you to parse XML documents\n      stored in files, fields, or variables.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hni1665702758666__p_d136259e1_d136260e1_d136261e1\">The UXMLREADER acts as an intermediary between the SAX parser and a SAX event handler. To use the UXMLREADER you need to implement a component that handles SAX callback operations.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hni1665702758666__topic_d97042e1_d97043e1_d97044e1_d97045e1_d97046e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1139528e55\">Operations</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hni1665702758666__li_d48236e1_d48237e1_d48238e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kch1665703202145.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kch1665703202145.html\" title=\"Parses a specified XML stream.\">PARSE</a>—parses a\n               specified XML stream. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hni1665702758666__li_d48239e1_d48240e1_d48241e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ttv1665703202809.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ttv1665703202809.html\" title=\"Parses an XML document in the specified file.\">PARSEFILE</a>—parses an XML\n               document in the specified file.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hni1665702758666__li_d48233e1_d48234e1_d48235e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hwy1665703203214.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hwy1665703203214.html\" title=\"Specifies the component instance to serve as the SAX handler.\">SETHANDLER</a>—specifies the\n               component instance to serve as the SAX handler.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xjf1665702758735.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Creating a SAX Event Handler</a><p>Before starting to parse XML documents using the UXMLREADER component, you need to implement the operations that handle parser events, such as starting and ending the document and elements, and error handling.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqh1665702758875.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SAX Callback Operations</a><p>SAX callback operations are APIs that can be implemented on a user-defined SAX event handler. They enable you to use the parser information to manipulate and analyze XML data, and handle any errors that may be encountered.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wff1665702758803.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Reading and Parsing Customized XML</a><p>You can parse XML documents stored in files, fields, or variables using the UXMLREADER component API.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528297\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528297\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "UXMLREADER Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 UXMLREADER is an internal Uniface component that enables you to parse XML documents stored in files, fields, or variables. The UXMLREADER acts as an intermediary between the SAX parser and a SAX event handler. To use the UXMLREADER you need to implement a component that handles SAX callback operations. Operations PARSE —parses a specified XML stream. PARSEFILE —parses an XML document in the specified file. SETHANDLER —specifies the component instance to serve as the SAX handler. Related Links Creating a SAX Event Handler Before starting to parse XML documents using the UXMLREADER component, you need to implement the operations that handle parser events, such as starting and ending the document and elements, and error handling. SAX Callback Operations SAX callback operations are APIs that can be implemented on a user-defined SAX event handler. They enable you to use the parser information to manipulate and analyze XML data, and handle any errors that may be encountered. Reading and Parsing Customized XML You can parse XML documents stored in files, fields, or variables using the UXMLREADER component API. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}